  "description": "The recipe uses gentle seasoning and controlled oil so the grain, lentil, and vegetable flavors stay clear and clean. Vegetable Kambu Kozhukattai brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a saute pan on medium heat. Add mustard seeds and urad dal and cook until the dal is lightly golden. Stir in curry leaves, ginger, chilli, and the vegetable; cook 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in water and salt and bring to a full boil over high heat. Lower the heat and stir in the grain slowly until it forms a soft mass.",
    "Cover and rest off heat for 5 minutes. When cool enough to handle, shape into small oblong dumplings with damp hands.",
    "Steam on medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes until the surface looks matte and firm. Serve warm with chutney or a thin lentil broth."
  ],
